Journal:
--------

To speed up the calculation, I could discretize the image into values 0 - 9 and then create a dictionary
this dictionary represents the histogram. Subsequently when I move a moving-window through the image I can
subtract and add values to the dictionary in each step. That would be adding and removing 20 values in each step. 

It is possible there is a way to change the previously calculated variance instead of recalculating the variance in each step. 




